Dose-Response Descriptive Statistics

Jonathan Salas

Last Updated 30 July, 2024

Import the cleaned data - Point to the correct raw data directory

cleaned_res_dir <-"data/processed/cleaned_dr.RData"

Aesthetics

blank.plot <- theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.border = element_blank(), 
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(), #this theme section generates a blank canvas
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), 
        axis.line = element_line(colour = "black"),
        legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.justification="top")

Import Subject Data

load(cleaned_res_dir)

Descriptive Statistics

Summary Table of Subjects

cleaned_res |>
  count(waveform, voltage, pulse_seq) |> left_join(
    # Add in basic stats for depth/diameter
    cleaned_res |> group_by(waveform, voltage, pulse_seq) |>
      summarise(
        median_depth = median(depth, na.rm = T),
        IQR_depth = IQR(depth, na.rm = T),
        median_diameter = median(diameter, na.rm = T),
        IQR_diameter = IQR(diameter, na.rm = T),
        median_depth_per_width = median(depth_per_width, na.rm = T),
        IQR_depth_per_width = IQR(depth_per_width, na.rm = T)
      )
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'waveform', 'voltage'. You can override
## using the `.groups` argument.
## Joining with `by = join_by(waveform, voltage, pulse_seq)`
## # A tibble: 4 × 10
##   waveform    voltage pulse_seq     n median_depth IQR_depth median_diameter
##   <chr>       <chr>   <chr>     <int>        <dbl>     <dbl>           <dbl>
## 1 bipolar     10      20x5         30         5.25      1               17.4
## 2 fast-switch 10      10x5         60         4.15      5.05            13.9
## 3 unipolar    15      15x5         30        16         7.93            41  
## 4 unipolar    15      20x5         30        15.8       3               52

Plots

Make temporary mapping data

temp_mapping_dat <- cleaned_res |>
  filter(experiment_id != c("04022024Potato")) # excluded because this is the experiment where # of uni/bip pulses were changed sequentially, can't be compared to rest

Depth

Depth Dose-Response - Line Plots

temp_mapping_dat |>
  ggplot(data = _, aes(
    x = application_num,
    y = depth,
    group = id,
    color = id
  )) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  facet_wrap( ~ experiment_id + pulse_seq + waveform + voltage) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = temp_mapping_dat$application_num,
                     breaks = temp_mapping_dat$application_num) +
  scale_color_discrete(guide = "none") +
  ggtitle("Title") +
  xlab("Repetitions") +
  ylab("Depth (cm)") +
  labs(caption = "Caption") +
  scale_color_discrete(guide = "none") +
  blank.plot
## Scale for colour is already present.
## Adding another scale for colour, which will replace the existing scale.
## Warning: Removed 4 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

Depth Dose-Response - Smoothed Line Plots

temp_mapping_dat |>
  ggplot(data = _, aes(x = application_num, y = depth)) +
  geom_smooth(span = 10) +
  geom_point(aes(color=id)) +
  facet_wrap( ~ experiment_id + pulse_seq + waveform + voltage) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = temp_mapping_dat$application_num,
                     breaks = temp_mapping_dat$application_num) +
  scale_color_discrete(guide = "none") +
  ggtitle("Title") +
  xlab("Repetitions") +
  ylab("Depth (cm)") +
  labs(caption = "Caption") +
  blank.plot
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
